5. Ways to Reduce Manufacturing Costs While Maintaining Quality
1. Simplify Ingredient SKUs

Use overlapping ingredients across flavors.
Example:

Chocolate base used for multiple variants
Same frosting base with different toppings

This lowers inventory waste and sourcing complexity.

2. Increase Batch Sizes

Larger production runs reduce:

Setup costs
Labor inefficiency
Packaging waste

Even moving from 500 → 2,000 units can significantly reduce unit cost.

3. Source Packaging in Bulk

Custom cans and labels become much cheaper at higher quantities.
Negotiate:

Annual contracts
Volume discounts
Shared packaging dimensions
4. Reduce Shipping Weight

Lighter cans and optimized box sizes reduce:

Freight charges
Storage costs
Fulfillment expenses
5. Start With Fewer Flavors

Launch with 3–4 bestselling flavors first instead of 10.
Benefits:

Lower ingredient waste
Easier forecasting
Simpler production planning
Better operational efficiency

A focused menu usually improves margins during early-stage validation.
